<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="140" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="12.[267,641,545,569]" box="[267,641,545,569]" pageId="12" pageNumber="140">
<heading bold="true" box="[267,641,545,569]" centered="true" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="12" pageNumber="140" reason="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[267,641,545,569]" pageId="12" pageNumber="140">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Blanchard" baseAuthorityYear="1851" box="[267,480,545,569]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Achilia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="valdiviensis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[267,480,545,569]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="140">Achilia valdiviensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,756,593,840]" pageId="12" pageNumber="140">
<bibRefCitation author="Jeannel R." box="[151,370,593,616]" pageId="12" pageNumber="140" pagination="295 - 479" refId="ref22040" refString="Jeannel R. 1962. Les Pselaphides de la Paleantarctide Occidentale [pp. 295 - 479]. In: Deboutteville C. D., E. Rapoport (eds), Biologie de l'Amerique Australe. Vol. I. Etude sur la Faune du Sol. Centre National de la Recherche Scientifique, Paris." type="book chapter" year="1962">Jeannel (1962: 398</bibRefCitation>
, 424) characterized this group as follows: elytra with 3 basal foveae; basal striae of first abdominal tergite separated by about a third of the tergal width; clypeus of the male head protruding in the form of a duck bill; antennae of the male with enlarged pedicel; distal end of longitudinal struts of aedeagus spatulate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="140" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,756,593,840]" lastBlockId="12.[831,1437,258,409]" pageId="12" pageNumber="140">
The group includes 
<taxonomicName authority="(Blanchard, 1851)" baseAuthorityName="Blanchard" baseAuthorityYear="1851" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Achilia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="valdiviensis">
<emphasis box="[394,614,785,808]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="140">Achilia valdiviensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Blanchard C. E." pageId="12" pageNumber="140" pagination="1 - 564" refId="ref21916" refString="Blanchard C. E. 1851. Fauna Chilena, Insectos, Coleopteros. LVI. Pselafianos [pp. 561 - 564]. In: Gay C., Historia fisica y politica de Chile. Zoologia, 5: 1 - 564 + ii, pls 1 - 32." type="journal article" year="1851">Blanchard, 1851</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Jeannel, 1962" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1962" box="[264,537,817,840]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Achilia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kuscheli">
<emphasis box="[264,381,817,840]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="140">A. kuscheli</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Jeannel R." box="[387,537,817,840]" pageId="12" pageNumber="140" pagination="295 - 479" refId="ref22040" refString="Jeannel R. 1962. Les Pselaphides de la Paleantarctide Occidentale [pp. 295 - 479]. In: Deboutteville C. D., E. Rapoport (eds), Biologie de l'Amerique Australe. Vol. I. Etude sur la Faune du Sol. Centre National de la Recherche Scientifique, Paris." type="book chapter" year="1962">Jeannel, 1962</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Howewer our study of the 
<typeStatus box="[895,941,258,281]" pageId="12" pageNumber="140">type</typeStatus>
material revealed that 
<taxonomicName authority="Jeannel, 1962" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Achilia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kuscheli">
<emphasis box="[1176,1345,258,281]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="140">Achilia kuscheli</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Jeannel R." pageId="12" pageNumber="140" pagination="295 - 479" refId="ref22040" refString="Jeannel R. 1962. Les Pselaphides de la Paleantarctide Occidentale [pp. 295 - 479]. In: Deboutteville C. D., E. Rapoport (eds), Biologie de l'Amerique Australe. Vol. I. Etude sur la Faune du Sol. Centre National de la Recherche Scientifique, Paris." type="book chapter" year="1962">Jeannel, 1962</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Blanchard, 1851)" baseAuthorityName="Blanchard" baseAuthorityYear="1851" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Achilia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="valdiviensis">
<emphasis box="[1277,1436,290,313]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="140">A. valdiviensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Blanchard C. E." box="[839,1035,322,345]" pageId="12" pageNumber="140" pagination="1 - 564" refId="ref21916" refString="Blanchard C. E. 1851. Fauna Chilena, Insectos, Coleopteros. LVI. Pselafianos [pp. 561 - 564]. In: Gay C., Historia fisica y politica de Chile. Zoologia, 5: 1 - 564 + ii, pls 1 - 32." type="journal article" year="1851">Blanchard, 1851</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1076,1186,322,345]" pageId="12" pageNumber="140">syn. nov</emphasis>
.). Consequently the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Blanchard" baseAuthorityYear="1851" box="[831,994,354,377]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Achilia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="valdiviensis">
<emphasis box="[831,994,354,377]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="140">A. valdiviensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group now holds only 
<taxonomicName authority="(Blanchard, 1851)" baseAuthorityName="Blanchard" baseAuthorityYear="1851" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Achilia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="valdiviensis">
<emphasis box="[1274,1436,354,377]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="140">A. valdiviensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Blanchard C. E." box="[839,1020,386,409]" pageId="12" pageNumber="140" pagination="1 - 564" refId="ref21916" refString="Blanchard C. E. 1851. Fauna Chilena, Insectos, Coleopteros. LVI. Pselafianos [pp. 561 - 564]. In: Gay C., Historia fisica y politica de Chile. Zoologia, 5: 1 - 564 + ii, pls 1 - 32." type="journal article" year="1851">Blanchard, 1851</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
